@Node AUPRINT "STCCG.guide/Alternate Universe/Printing Run"
@TOC AU

    @{b}@{u}Alternate Universe Printing Run@{ub}@{uu}

The alternate universe consists of 122 cards including
    40 Common Cards
    40 Uncommon Cards
    41 Rare Cards
     1 Ultra-rare card (The @{"Future Enterprise" link "XXPATH:federation.guide/FUTENT"})

Packaging of the cards is in 15-card expansion packs and uses the same
randomizing method used for the original set. (No secondary sorting).

In each expansion pack you should find:
    11 Common Cards
     3 Uncommon Cards
     1 Rare (or Ultra-rare) Card

The overall print run for the Alternate Universe set was
    @{b}76 838 760@{ub} cards

This is
      @{b}42335@{ub} of the @{"Future Enterprise" link "XXPATH:federation.guide/FUTENT"}
     @{b}127006@{ub} of each rare card      (or  @{b}5207255@{ub} total)
     @{b}381019@{ub} of each uncommon card  (or @{b}15240746@{ub} total)
    @{b}1408711@{ub} of each common card    (or @{b}56348424@{ub} total)

The Ultra-rare card @{"Future Enterprise" link "XXPATH:federation.guide/FUTENT"} is exactly three times as
scarce as a rare card.

The Rare card @{"Ophidian Cane" link "XXPATH:artifact.guide/OPHCANE"} is printed with the uncommon cards, but also
three times as scarce. So in each pack with an @{"Ophidian Cane" link "XXPATH:artifact.guide/OPHCANE"} you will get
two Rare cards (but only two Uncommon cards)!

@EndNode

